extends ../layout

block content
  section#heartwheels.section
    .container
      h2 Heartwheels

      p.
        Taku Hanson was one of the most special members of our Sea Hawkers family — a prior
        Seahawker of the Month who embodied everything this community stands for. Even while
        fighting his own battle with stage 4 cancer, Taku created Heartwheels with a simple
        goal: make sure every child being treated at Montana's only cancer center received a
        Hot Wheels toy to play with during treatment and take home.

      p.
        In a single year he donated 2,500 cars, and had already collected over 5,000 more
        when he passed away. The program grew into something even bigger — adult cancer patients
        began bringing cars to give to the kids receiving chemo alongside them, lifting the
        spirits of the entire cancer ward.

      p.
        Taku was also a veteran who spent his time visiting other veterans in the hospital,
        especially those who had no one else. He volunteered across the community — supporting
        adults with Down Syndrome, helping local animal shelters — all while undergoing his
        own treatment.

      p.
        His legacy continues today, lovingly carried forward by Brenda. Rest easy, Taku.
        You made the world a better place.

  section.section.alt-bg
    .container
      h3 Photos

      .gallery-grid.gallery-grid--3col
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/7932613618454906383.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/IMG_0010.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/IMG_0011.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/IMG_9719.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/IMG_9720.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")
        img(src="/img/heartwheels/IMG_9726.jpeg" alt="Heartwheels donation" loading="lazy")

  section.section
    .container
      h3 Keep Heartwheels Going

      p.
        Want to honor Taku's legacy by helping put a Hot Wheels car in the hands of a child
        going through cancer treatment? Bring new toys to a watch party or mail them to Brenda.

      .cards.cards-three
        .card
          .card-body
            h3 Bring to a Watch Party
            p.
              Drop off new, unopened Hot Wheels — or other small toys — at any of our game day
              watch parties. YSH will handle shipping them to Brenda for you.
            a.btn-outline(href="/#contact") Find a Watch Party
        .card
          .card-body
            h3 Send Cars
            p Mail new, unopened Hot Wheels cars directly to Brenda. Every car makes a difference.
            button.btn-outline(type="button" data-modal="address-modal") Mailing Address
        .card
          .card-body
            h3 Spread the Word
            p.
              Share Heartwheels with friends, family, and your community. The more people
              who know, the more cars we can deliver.
            button.btn-outline#hw-share-btn(type="button" hidden) Share
        .card
          .card-body
            h3 Questions?
            p.
              Reach out through our contact form if you'd like to get involved in another way.
            a.btn-outline(href="/#contact") Get in Touch

  section.section.alt-bg
    .container
      a.btn-outline(href="/#charitable") &larr; Back to Charitable Work

  #address-modal.hw-modal(role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="address-modal-title")
    .hw-modal-backdrop
    .hw-modal-dialog
      button.hw-modal-close(type="button" aria-label="Close") &times;
      h3#address-modal-title Mailing Address
      address.
        Brenda Rosler-Hanson
        #[br] 278 2nd Ave W N
        #[br] Kalispell, MT 59901

  script(src="/js/heartwheels.js")
